\left( {u,v} \right) = \int\limits_0^1 {uv} dx
v
v \in {V^0} = \left\{ {\omega :\left\| \omega  \right\| + \left\| {\omega '} \right\| < \infty ,\omega \left( 0 \right) = 0,\omega \left( 1 \right) = 0} \right\}
\int\limits_0^1 { - u''v} dx = \left[ { - u'v} \right]_{x = 0}^{x = 1} + \int\limits_0^1 {u'v'} dx =  - u'\left( 1 \right)\underbrace {v\left( 1 \right)}_{ = 0} + u'\left( 0 \right)v\underbrace {\left( 0 \right)}_{ = 0} + \int\limits_0^1 {u'v'} dx = \int\limits_0^1 {u'v'} dx
